,"variants":[{"name":"Summerton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Somerton, particularly in Oxfordshire and Somerset, but also in Lincolnshire and Norfolk, named with Old English <i>sumor</i> ‘summer’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Muriell","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin (  see  Muireall   ). Forms of the name are found in Breton as well as in Irish and Scottish Gaelic, and in the form   Meriel   it was in use in the heart of England in the Middle Ages. The surname <i>Merrill</i> is derived from it. As <i>Muriel</i> it was at first used mainly in Scotland, but became more widely popular during the first half of the 20th century. Since then it has fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":65,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":78,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Muriell Somerton was born about 1250, in Somerton, Norfolk, England, her father, Robert Somerton Esquire, was 28 and her mother, Mrs Robert Somerton, was 24. She married Nicholas Clere in 1270, in Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1250–":"umbes 1250–Surnud","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1224–Male":"1224–Surnud","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1228":"1228","1315":"1315","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","before 1250":"enne 1250","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England":"Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England","England":"England","Somerton, Norfolk, England":"Somerton, Norfolk, England","Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England":"Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1250–":"noin 1250–Kuollut","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1224–Male":"1224–Kuollut","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1315":"1315","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","before 1250":"ennen vuotta 1250","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England":"Caistor Saint Edmunds, Norfolk, England","England":"England","Somerton, Norfolk, England":"Somerton, Norfolk, England","Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England":"Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, England"},"